Privacy Policy for Shadow Leap
Effective Date: 09/03/2025

Shadow Leap values your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines the types of information we collect, how we use it, and your rights regarding your data.

1. Information We Collect
1.1 Automatically Collected Information:
When you use our app, we may collect limited information such as:

Device information (e.g., device model, operating system, and app version).
Usage data (e.g., session duration and features accessed).
1.2 Data You Provide:
The app does not require you to create an account or share personal information such as your name or email. However, if you contact us for support, we may collect:

Your email address.
The details of your query.
1.3 Third-Party Services:
If our app integrates third-party analytics or ads, these services may collect and process additional information. Refer to their privacy policies for more details.

2. How We Use Your Information
We use the collected data for:

Improving app performance and user experience.
Identifying and fixing technical issues.
Providing customer support, if requested.

3. Data Sharing
We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information. However, we may share anonymized or aggregated data with third-party services for:

Analytics (e.g., to understand app usage trends).
Advertising (if applicable).

4. Data Storage and Security
We implement industry-standard measures to protect your data from unauthorized access or misuse. However, no method of transmission or storage is entirely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

5. Your Rights
You have the right to:

Request a copy of your personal data (if any).
Request that we delete your data, subject to legal or operational obligations.

6. Third-Party Links
The app may contain links to external websites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of these third-party websites.

7. Updates to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted within the app, and the effective date will be updated accordingly.

8. Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
